Once these manufacturing and information practices have been adopted, it should come as no surprise that they affect the performance of business <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">units</ENAMEX>. Based on our survey research, we found that implementing a combination of the <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">four</NUMEX> key practices‚Äîbar codes, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">EDI</ENAMEX>, advanced shipping systems, and modular assembly‚Äîincreases business-unit performance because these practices interact with and reinforce one another. This is sometimes described as <ENAMEX TYPE="DISEASE">‚Äúcomplementarities‚Äù</ENAMEX> between practices. The specific sequence of adoption should also affect performance outcomes.
